**PCoA Plots- Aitchison Distance** 
#See the MicroViz tutorial for all the great addons you can use to customize your ordination plots: https://david-barnett.github.io/microViz/articles/web-only/ordination.html 
```{r}
ps1_ord <- ps1m %>% tax_filter(min_prevalence = 0.05, tax_level = "Genus") #Ordinations don't do too well with taxa that are really low in relative abundance in only a couple of samples. Here we are selecting for taxa that are atleast prevelent in 5% of our samples. HOW YOU FILTER WILL DEPEND ON YOUR SAMPLES. 

#Note: We are using an aitchison distance matrix for the PCoA plot. This requires the data are center-log ratio (CLR) transformed; HOWEVER, the code below automatically does this when the aitchison distance matrix is applied. I am writing this note to say that you do not need to clr transform prior to this code.

#ASV-level
ps1_ord %>%
  tax_transform("identity") %>%
  dist_calc(dist = "aitchison") %>%
  ord_calc("PCoA") %>%
  ord_plot(color = "pool_corrected", shape = "medium_simple", size = 2) +
  scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Dark2")

#Genus-level (with some extra funky add-ons)
pcoa_genus<-ps1_ord %>%
  tax_transform("identity", rank = "Genus") %>%
  dist_calc(dist = "aitchison") %>%
  ord_calc("PCoA") %>%
  ord_plot(color = "pool_corrected", shape = "medium", size = 2) +
  scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Dark2")
pcoa_genus + labs(color = "Pool", shape = "Medium") +
  theme_bw() +
  ggside::geom_xsideboxplot(aes(fill = medium, y = medium), orientation = "y") +
  ggside::geom_ysideboxplot(aes(fill = medium, x = medium), orientation = "x") +
  ggside::scale_xsidey_discrete(labels = NULL) +
  ggside::scale_ysidex_discrete(labels = NULL) +
  ggside::theme_ggside_void()
dev.off()
```

